<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-changing-quadratic-parameters">

	<statement>
		<p>
	      Open a browser and point it to <url href="https://www.desmos.com/calculator"><em>Desmos</em></url>.
	      In <em>Desmos</em>, enter <c>q(x) = ax^2 + bx + c</c>;
	      you will be prompted to add sliders for <m>a</m>, <m>b</m>,
	      and <m>c</m>.  Do so.
	      Then begin exploring with the sliders and respond to the following questions.			
		</p>

		<p>
			<ol marker="a.">
		        <li>
		          <p>
		            Describe how changing the value of <m>a</m> impacts the graph of <m>q</m>.
		          </p>
		        </li>

		        <li>
		          <p>
		            Describe how changing the value of <m>b</m> impacts the graph of <m>q</m>.
		          </p>
		        </li>

		        <li>
		          <p>
		            Describe how changing the value of <m>c</m> impacts the graph of <m>q</m>.
		          </p>
		        </li>

		        <li>
		          <p>
		            Which parameter seems to have the simplest effect?
		            Which parameter seems to have the most complicated effect?
		            Why?
		          </p>
		        </li>

		        <li>
		          <p>
		            Is it possible to find a formula for a quadratic function that passes through the points <m>(0,8)</m>,
		            <m>(1,12)</m>, <m>(2,12)</m>?  If yes, do so; if not, explain why not.
		          </p>
		        </li>
			</ol>
		</p>
